<TITLE> EC receives total 388 appeals, validates 67 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)  The Election Commission validated 37 more nominations after hearing appeals against their cancellation on Sunday, bringing the total to 67 in two days, EC officials said. The commission received a total of 388 appeals up to Sunday's 5pm deadline. "Of the total, 307 were against cancellation of nominations and 81 against validation of candidacies by returning officers," EC deputy secretary (law) AKM Salimullah told bdnews24.com. A total of 557 nominations were initially rejected by the EC after two days of scrutiny on Dec 3-4. Hearings on appeals against the rejections began Saturday. EC joint secretary Rafiqul Islam told bdnews24.com Sunday: "Nearly 200 appeals against cancellations were heard over the past two days." CEC ATM Shamsul Huda, commissioners Sohul Hossain and M Sakhawat Hossin, EC secretary Humayun Kabir, joint secretary NI Khan and deputy secretaries Jasmine Tuly and AKM Salimullah were present during the hearings. "From Monday onward until Dec. 11, Hearings will take place on appeals against defaulting borrowers, convicted and also validations of candidacy when a final list of candidates will be announced," EC secretary Humayun Kabir told bdnews24.com. Some 1,899 of a total of 2,456 nominations filed were initially validated by returning officers. The last day for withdrawal of candidacy is Dec. 11. The deadline for submission of nomination papers was Nov. 30. bdnews
